column4: Anyone know how to get the normal Gnome desktop on UNR 9.10?  The desktop-switcher is missing...
sudo apt-get purge netbook-launcher && sudo apt-get purge maximus && sudo apt-get autoremove && sudo reboot
ya think?  i'll give it a shot..
well, yes.. the netbook launcher is gone.. but i've got no menu or icons or right-click menu.
thanks for your help... do you happen to know how I can get 'places' and 'system' up there on the menubar?
add applet name gnome custom menu
is that supposed to be under 'add to panel'?  I got the 'main menu' - the main GNOME menu.
it's not there.. do i need to install it, maybe?
it's called 'menu bar' - a custom menu bar
ok then have you now got things?
have made a note of what I did so I can help others here, later... i've seen my question a lot
and if you want to install again then install thos two packages again
